cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI 

This paper deals with the recognition of handwritten characters, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the effectiveness of different feature sets, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Finally, the paper proposes a new feature set that significantly improves the recognition performance, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
